childMarkdownRemark.html: Worry less about security, caching, and talking to the server. Static sites are the new thing.
Your very first content with Contentful, pulled in JSON format using the Content Delivery API.
Webhooks notify you, another person or system when resources have changed by calling a given HTTP endpoint.

node.name: Reading Length
node.shortDescription: Book search engine built with vanilla NodeJS. Impressive usage statistics with over 80,000 unique visitors per month.

node.name: Bridger Putnam
node.shortDescription: My portfolio site, built with a GatsbyJS front-end hosted on Netlify using GraphQL to get data from a Contentful CMS backend. This site is FAST.

node.name: Sick Fits
node.shortDescription: Example eCommerce site built with NextJS, Apollo, and GraphQL (Yoga and Prisma.io). In other words, I built it myself without using any sort of eCommerce platform.

node.name: Catch of the Day
node.shortDescription: Menu website for a fictional restaurant I built using plain old React and Firebase as a backend.

node.name: LitBook
node.shortDescription: Work in progress. A place for readers to track what they're reading and organize book clubs. Spinoff from Reading Length.

shortBio.shortBio: Bridger is a full stack developer and web designer, striving to make a living off of coding so he can have more time in the day to enjoy mountain biking, hiking, skiing, and rock climbing. His focus is on developing websites that are fast and accessible.
